CC  Members of this family always occur in genomes with the preprotein translocase SecA (TIGR00963) and closely resemble it, hence the designation SecA2. However, this appears to mark a different type of accessory Sec system SecA2 (TIGR03714) from the serine-rich glycoprotein type found in Staphylococcus and Streptococcus, and the actinobacterial SecA2 (TIGR04221). This type occurs in species including Bacillus anthracis, Geobacillus thermoglucosidasius, Solibacillus silvestris, etc.
